## This is mgcv 1.8-33. For overview type 'help("mgcv-package")'.
correct_temp <- function(data, formula, gam_formula) {

  print("glm")
  model <- gam(as.formula(formula), 
               data = data,
               method = "REML")
  par(mfrow = c(2,2))
 # plot(model)
  par(mfrow = c(1,1))
  pred <- ggeffects::ggpredict(model, 
                                terms = "YEAR",
                                condition = c(NUMLEN = 1))
  print(pred)

  cat("\n\n")
  # plot(pred) %>% print()
  # cat("\n\n")
  
  print("gam")
  model2 <- gam(as.formula(gam_formula), 
            data = data,
            method = "REML")
  gam.check(model2)
    par(mfrow = c(2,2))
  plot(model2, all.terms = TRUE, rug = TRUE) %>%
    try()
  par(mfrow = c(1,1))
  pred2 <- ggeffects::ggpredict(model2, 
                                terms = "YEAR",
                                condition = c(NUMLEN = 1))
  print(pred2)
  cat("\n\n")
  # plot(pred2) %>% print()
  # cat("\n\n")
  
  compare_data <- rbind(pred %>% dplyr::mutate(type = "GLM"),
                        pred2 %>% dplyr::mutate(type = "GAM"))
  
  plt <- compare_data %>%
    ggplot2::ggplot(ggplot2::aes(x = x %>%
                                   as.character() %>%
                                   as.numeric(),
                                 y = predicted,
                                 color = type,
                                 group = type)) +
    ggplot2::geom_line() +
    ggplot2::geom_point() +
    ggplot2::theme_bw()
  
  print(plt)
  
  # plot(pred$x, pred$predicted, type = "b")
  # points(pred2$x, pred2$predicted, col = "red")
  # lines(pred2$x, pred2$predicted, col = "red")
  
  AIC(model, model2)
}

dat <- readRDS(here::here("data-raw/nmfs_survey_expanded_9c.RDS"))

dat <- dat %>%
    # make sure each year has enough of a spread of data
    dplyr::group_by(YEAR, size_group) %>% 
    dplyr::mutate(range_doy = max(DOY) - min(DOY)) %>%
    dplyr::filter(range_doy > 19)

  dplyr::mutate(MONTH = lubridate::month(EST_TOWDATE),
                WEEK = lubridate::week(EST_TOWDATE)) %>%
  dplyr::filter(WEEK %in% c(10:12, 37:43)) %>% # march, sept, oct
